      <div class="panel-body">
        <h3>Step 1: Boil</h3>
        <ul>
        <li>Fill your boil kettle with 3 gallons of clear, cold water. No warm water - we don't want any weird shit from your hot water heater screwing with the water chemistry.</li>
        <li>Heating this much water will take awhile. So go drink a beer in the meantime.</li>
        <li>Once your water is boiled, turn off the heat and REMOVE THE KETTLE FROM THE HEAT SOURCE.</li>
        <li>Drop in each of your fermentable ingredients one at a time, stirring them in carefully as you do. The liquid malt extract likes to scorch to the bottom of the kettle, so stir constantly when adding this. This is easier with two people. Meanwhile, the dry malt extract likes to clump up, so add it slowly as well.</li>
        </ul>

